Rating: 4
Hastings varied this somewhat in his recipe published from his appearance at the Atlanta Food and Wine Festival in 2012. In that version, he adds a 1/2 cup mirepoix (equal parts finely diced carrot, celery, onion). He also adds 3 Tblsp lemon juice and uses twice the amount of butter. Country Ham is used instead of prosciutto . I made it per the Atlanta recipe. It was wonderfully rich and 5-star. However, next time I will cut the butter (it doesn't have to be that rich) and cut back by half on the lemon juice as the lemon was too prominent. This recipe is the best Shrimp and Grits I've had in years.

