This is a great recipe to start with. I severely bastardized it but it still turned out DELICIOUS! Grits: Used half & half, and 1/2 the butter called for. Threw in some fresh corn at the end (a must--so delicious!). It turned out a little bit thick so I would probably add more water or chicken stock next time. Maybe try low-fat milk instead of half & half. Shrimp: Didn't use very much butter, used lots of garlic & shallots, threw in leftover sausage & pancetta instead of proscuitto, used fiery tomatoes, and threw in some leftover red wine. I wish there was more sauce...maybe some tomato sauce or something next time. All in all, it was sooooo tasty and I will definitely make this again soon.

