Grits and polenta are NOT the same thing! Both are corn, but grits are much more coarse. Try the grits from Anson Mill in South Carolina -- well worth the 1 1/2 hour cooking time. Their polenta is excellent as well. I buy it right from the mill and it is shipped directly to my home. Look up the mill on the web. Once you try it you'll never want the supermarket variety again!

